value.0: The intense heat of the chasm begins to fade, shielded by the massive columns that divide the cavern. As the tunnel forks and opens up into a huge chamber, blue firelight dances across the sulfuric field, painting shifting shadows along the stone features. Perhaps that also accounts for the smell of rotten egg that has been steadying increasing...

The heated air here is stifling and obscured with ash. Though it seems as though the lava trench snaking through this chasm has not seen any very recent activity, the ground is still warm - and some sections are blisteringly hot. The passage of the molten flow has left new rock in its wake; some in jagged chunks, others in sleek, flaking layers, but all of it exceptionally sharp and unwelcoming. 

A vicious heat spills out from further down the trench, and occasional flares of fire or a hissing pop of spit magma plays angry flares of light upon the rocks and throughout the ash that covers everything.
There is nothing special about this object.

This scree is unusual in that the rock fragments it is composed of are noticeably different from all of the other stone in the area. It seems to be from some other cave, but does not appear as if it was transported here by any intelligent design.

Curiously, the air is marginally more fresh and cool in this alcove. Looking up, there is a deep gouge in the cavern ceiling that extends up and out of the range of illumination and Darkvision. Given the position of the hole, it is reasonable to assume that the scree fell from there. But what lies beyond that, and the ultimate source of the out-of-place rock is not readily apparent.
These jutting, tendril-like mineral formations appear to be some kind of greenstone, but they are likely too brittle and delicate to be of very much use.

A glimmer of platinum...
